  "texts": [
    "They propose a method to enforce this constraint using a constrained optimization problem, penalizing models with disparate impacts on different groups while maximizing overall accuracy.",
    "Other than thresholding, causal methods can ensure model fairness by analyzing and modeling the causal relationships between input features, the predicted outcome, and the sensitive attribute.",
    "The goal is to identify the direct and indirect causal relationships between these variables and to use this information to create fair and unbiased models.",
    "In this context, Salimi et al.",
    "propose that repairing the training data to remove unfair causal relationships is more efficient than implementing correlation-based fairness metrics to address the root causes of unfairness."
  ],
